OL,6,F"But, most importantly, I would urge
OL,7,Fyou to listen to the voices of
OL,8,Fterminally ill Scots desperate for
OL,9,Fmore choice, control and dignity.
OL,11,F"This Bill has been a long time coming
OL,12,Fbut it does now offer the chance to
OL,13,Fprovide that compassionate choice for
OL,14,Fthe small number of terminally ill
OL,15,FScots who need it."
OL,17,FDr Miro Griffiths, spokesman for
OL,18,FBetter Way, said: "As a disabled
OL,19,Fperson and academic, I fear the
OL,20,Fconsequences of an assisted suicide
OL,21,Flaw.
