OL,6,F"Polling clearly shows that the public
OL,7,Fhave serious concerns about the
OL,8,Fimplications of a law change for
OL,9,Fvulnerable groups ` even people who
OL,10,Fmight support it in principle.
OL,12,F"Legislating for this practice would
OL,13,Fsend a regressive message that
OL,14,Fdisabled people's lives are not worth
OL,15,Fliving. Disabled people and others
OL,16,Fwould inevitably choose to end their
OL,17,Flives because they don't have access
OL,18,Fto support. This outcome is
OL,19,Funconscionable.
